webResources.textAttributionSnippet: (en) View of Lköpping in the summer of 1864. Dominating in the picture, the cathedral rises with its so-called Hårleman tower, which was replaced with the present after a major redevelopment from 1877. In front of the church is seen the city’s textwork, now city hall, which at the time was just completed. The other habitation to mention is the castle to the left of the church and the old upper secondary school house to the right of the work. The latter building served from 1810 as a logroom for Lköpping’s Masons - https://www.europeana.eu/item/73/S_OM_photo_OMEA0001240113. Östergötlands museum - http://digitaltmuseum.se/021017422234. Public Domain Mark - http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/mark/1.0/
